<header>
<p class="category">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/white-house" target="_blank">White House</a></p>
<h1>
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/30/trump-north-korea-1390738" target="_top">Trump’s made-for-TV moment in North Korea</a></h1>
<p class="subhead">In 2017, Trump tried to go to the DMZ to thump his chest at North Korea. On Sunday, he went to extend an olive branch.</p>
</header>
<footer class="meta">
<footer class="meta">
<div itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
<meta itemprop="name" content="Anita Kumar" />
<meta itemprop="email" content="" />
</div>
<p class="byline">
By <a href="https://www.politico.com/staff/anita-kumar" rel="author" class="url fn" target="_top">ANITA KUMAR</a></p>
 <p class="timestamp"><time itemprop="datePublished" datetime='2019-06-30 08:33:55'>06/30/2019 08:33 AM EDT</time></p>
<p class="updated">
Updated <time datetime='2019-06-30 17:15:35'>06/30/2019 05:15 PM EDT</time></p>
<span class="is-hidden" itemprop="dateModified">2019-06-30T05:15-0400</span>
</footer></footer>
</div>
</div>
<p>SEOUL, South Korea — In 2017, President Donald Trump secretly planned to walk right up to the North Korean border to show Kim Jong Un that America would stand up to his brutal regime. </p>
<p>In 2019, Trump publicly implored Kim to meet him at that same border in order to smile, shake hands and discuss the future the two countries could bring about together. </p><p class="story-full">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/06/30/trump-north-korea-1390738" target="_top">Read More &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</article>
