<header>
<p class="category">
Defense</p>
<h1>
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/05/27/north-korea-bolton-warmonger-1345029" target="_top">North Korea calls Bolton a ‘defective human product’</a></h1>
</header>
<footer class="meta">
<footer class="meta">
<div itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
<meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press" />
<meta itemprop="email" content="" />
</div>
<p class="byline">
By ASSOCIATED PRESS</p>
<p class="timestamp"><time itemprop="datePublished" datetime='2019-05-27 00:00:48'>05/27/2019 12:00 AM EDT</time></p>
<p class="updated">
Updated <time datetime='2019-05-27 00:24:51'>05/27/2019 12:24 AM EDT</time></p>
<span class="is-hidden" itemprop="dateModified">2019-05-27T12:24-0400</span>
</footer></footer>
</div>
</div>
<p>SEOUL, South Korea — North Korea on Monday called U.S. National Security Adviser John Bolton a “warmonger” and “defective human product” after he called the North’s recent tests of short-range missile a violation of U.N. Security Council resolutions.</p>
<p>The statement by an unnamed North Korean foreign ministry spokesman came as President Donald Trump continued his visit to Japan for meetings with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe in which the nuclear standoff with North Korea was expected to be high on the agenda.</p><p class="story-full">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/05/27/north-korea-bolton-warmonger-1345029" target="_top">Read More &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</article>
