<div class="summary">
<header>
<h1>
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/04/24/kim-jong-un-russia-korea-1289643" target="_top">Smiling Kim arrives by train in Russia for his Putin summit</a></h1>
</header>
<footer class="meta">
<footer class="meta">
<div itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
<meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press" />
<meta itemprop="email" content="" />
</div>
<p class="byline">
By ASSOCIATED PRESS</p>
<p class="timestamp"><time itemprop="datePublished" datetime='2019-04-24 19:24:03'>04/24/2019 07:24 PM EDT</time></p>
<p class="updated">
Updated <time datetime='2019-04-24 20:01:10'>04/24/2019 08:01 PM EDT</time></p>
<span class="is-hidden" itemprop="dateModified">2019-04-24T08:01-0400</span>
</footer></footer>
</div>
</div>
<p>VLADIVOSTOK, Russia — A smiling and upbeat Kim Jong Un arrived Wednesday in far-eastern Russia aboard an armored train for a much-anticipated summit with Russian President Vladimir Putin that comes amid deadlocked global diplomacy over the North Korean leader’s nuclear program.</p>
<p>Both leaders have high hopes for their first one-on-one meeting: Kim for a win after his failed second summit with U.S. President Donald Trump and Putin for a chance to raise Moscow’s clout in the region and gain more leverage with Washington.</p><p class="story-full">
<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2019/04/24/kim-jong-un-russia-korea-1289643" target="_top">Read More &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
